"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-09-China-s-Wu-Peng-talks-about-his-Paris-2024-men-s-speed-climbing-silver-1vVjKs8iSbe-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  China's Wu Peng earned the silver medal in men's sport climbing's\\u00a0speed event at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics on Thursday, clocking 4.77 seconds, just 0.02 seconds behind Veddriq Leonardo, who won Indonesia's first gold in Paris, with Sam Watson of the USA rounding out the podium.  Shortly after his competition, the 21-year-old Wu and Zhong Qixin, the head coach of China's speed climbing team, spoke to CGTN Sports Scene's Greg Laffradi about Wu's achievement, as well as the success of Deng Lijuan, who took silver in the women's event one day earlier.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"